He carried under his arm a file with three new rental contracts for three apartments: his own, that of his daughter and his son who is serving a sentence.
Deregulation has increased the rent for these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 apartment of the second category 4100 crowns.
&quot;And there is no hot water and the heating runs on solid fuel,&quot; the man with signing authority points to his son&#39;s new contract.
“But I signed anyway,” he explains, half angry and half resigned.
Citizens&#39; Association of Apartments BytyOKD.cz, which has described the new rental conditions as &#39;immoral and indecent&#39;, advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be published explaining the method to follow to claim.
But the man reacts to this with a wave of his hand.
&quot;One says that, the other says something else&quot; frowning.
