The kindergarten is also part of the offices, including the architects.
the Avriopoint administrative building in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
Nobody could have expected that it also houses a mini kindergarten with all the right things - colored walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October last year, the children of Arch employees can go there. design.
The project-architectural company Arch. Design. whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, imagined his mini company kindergarten from the first sketches of the Avriopoint building.
It employs around 90 people, mostly of childbearing age, and it was important to her that female architects and project managers be able to return to work quickly.
Along with reduced-time work contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by the Arch company. Design. as part of its social program.
Builders and architects thus have the possibility of combining demanding work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design.themselves who imagined this nursery school and with the support of the management they were able to obtain a grant from the European Union and the Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs.
The mini kindergarten is financed by means of the European Social Fund through the operational program of human resources and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to funding allocations (up to 2.8 mil.de Czech crowns). They were able to buy equipment and devices and after two years provide qualified personnel and start-up.
After using the funding grant (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and it was the company Economy rating which helped to apply for the grant.
Care for the children is provided by qualified staff, all day long a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of the children. children can go to kindergarten without any age limit, but most of them are over three years old.
As it is a &quot;mini kindergarten&quot; there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace each other.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all the employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is individual care and education, the mini kindergarten curriculum is comparable to that for preschool education.
The children don&#39;t just play there, but quality education is also provided - from the beginning to the preparation for the school benches, English is taught.
The classroom is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that the children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can control their child at any time and not have the stress of being late to pick up the children from a school far from the parents&#39; place of work.
Parents therefore use their work time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design. has thus registered among the companies which offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and which are friendly towards the family and through this program reinforces the HR marketing.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look inside Gaudi&#39;s interiors.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase resembles the spine of a dinosaur, and the balconies resemble the mouths of open fish.
This is how the house Casa Battlo in Barcelona by the architect Antoni Gaudi looks like.
Due to its organic shapes, the house has earned the nickname Bone House from the locals.
Organic shapes, wild colours, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaics, facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is typical for Antoni Gaudi&#39;s Art Nouveau.
The front facade of the house unfolds its dreamy lines, pleasant colors and textures that recall nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation one sees the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought out with precision.
At night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brilliant colors is enhanced.
The coiling and twisting of forms also appears in the interiors with equal measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the peephole and the slats.
The Battlo house which stands in the Eixample district in the Passeig de Gracia shopping street at number. 43, was born from the construction of a house in 1877 by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, initially insisted on demolishing the old building and building a brand new one but quickly accepted Gaudi&#39;s idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-unit house was not thought up by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that the decorations for a representative apartment of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade were born.
For the façade, other artists and designers also worked.
The joint work for the Casa Battlo house plans began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi&#39;s Casa Mila and Park Guell in which there are other works by Gaudi.
Locals dubbed the hot house right after it was finished because of its organic shapes &quot;the Bone House&quot;.
Others, with regard to the specific mechanism of opening the windows, have called it &quot;the house that yawns&quot;.
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint George the patron saint of Catalonia.
Other sculptural elements of the construction contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi designed a unique central heating system for the house, with ventilation vents and typical chimneys.
Their 45 degree inclination seems odd.
During the creation Gaudi completely disregarded the building guidelines of that time and did not allow himself to be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the building permit, knowing, of course, that the data given on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finishing the city council was horrified and asked for changes.
It did not please, for example, the members of the municipal council that the pillars of the building encroached on the public sidewalk.
There was never any modification, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call from the city Josep Battlo requested (and obtained satisfaction) the authorization to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room, and on the third a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase which leads to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were canceled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of linking spaces.
The common part can be completely connected by opening the doors of the lounges and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate conversations.
The house with Gaudi&#39;s reconstruction received besides new facades a non-traditional roof and two more floors.
Gaudi&#39;s play with light is also impressive, with the blue and white glazed tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with the skylights.
The two-color game gives maximum light to all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that the white reflects more than the dark which on the contrary absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house which was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous designer.
They continued the tours as they found it to be a lucrative business and they expanded the scope of tours to common areas and the attic including the roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist card holders get 20 percent off.
The sum is nevertheless above the price of entry in the other constructions of Gaudi in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you need to quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and completely visit the house.
How to choose a mattress and a box spring: women have different criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for sleeping, so the mattress and the box spring provide a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the choice several things are decisive: the weight, the height, the age, the state of health as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and box spring will be placed is also important.
A typical example?
For example in the country house where one does not sleep continuously latex mattresses are not suitable because they &quot;warm up&quot; slowly.
They also weigh more than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to turn them over frequently.
If they also do not have enough ventilation channels in the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain humidity. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also a determining factor in the choice.
Anyone who spends most of their time abroad, where very thick mattresses with a softening layer are frequently used, will hardly feel comfortable on a low, hard surface.
&quot;That&#39;s how all the hockey players coming back from the NHL complain that they can&#39;t sleep there.&quot;
&quot;For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam.&quot;
&quot;Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a nervous system disorder who therefore poorly assume &quot;information&quot; from the joints and the skin&quot;, explains Sylva Adamczikova who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That&#39;s why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered the hokeyists as well as other customers.
“Today everything is going well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico, for example, have suitable mattresses.
You don&#39;t have to be an NHL guy to enjoy lazy foam.
This &quot;miracle&quot; simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and its shape according to the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won&#39;t turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You just sleep better.
The lazy foam also works as a protection against pressure ulcers.
For the choice of mattress according to your height, add the length of the feet, which is approximately 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman with a height of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220cm.
The minimum width for each for a double bed should be 90 cm or a total of 180 cm.
For single beds, singles for example, it is recommended to take at least 120/140 cm.
It is convenient when visiting.
&#39;However there is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when lying on your back you should rest your hands comfortably with your elbows slightly bent. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Bourreliers-mattresses and decorators who has devoted herself for several years to the issue of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of furniture and teaches it in specialized schools.
For a double bed everyone needs their own box spring and mattress, so be careful when buying to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the bed base at different heights and this is not possible on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, from this count for the shape and ventilation layer at least three centimeters.
&quot;To the touch or while sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs&quot;, warns Héléna Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a specific type of box spring.
The box spring bed, when the mattress and the box spring are united like Siamese twins, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses ventilate very badly; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night we normally perspire from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years the mattress begins to resemble a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this, specialists refuse to advertise a 25-year lifespan for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But everything to his but.
And for that, a piece of advice from the sellers: for a 120/140cm mattress, forgo hygiene or washing for the mattress cover, but rather add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash. .
And although nowadays it is common to manufacture covers with zipper for the whole set, that is, after opening we have two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine this is very important!) otherwise the manipulation for the large models (and for one person) becomes when they are removed a fight between a lightweight and a heavyweight in a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a box spring?
Never!
Maximum for a bed intended for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) with ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with bag springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and an ventilation layer.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of such a bed.
For single position slatted bases with 14/18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are the ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are doubled in the lower part of the kidneys and it is thus possible to regulate their stiffness.
For mattresses with several positions, do not take a spring mattress because it does not respond to changes in position.
Besides adjusting the stiffness of the slats, a so-called shoulder cradle can also be installed.
This is a special connection of the slats which makes it possible to put pressure or even to tilt the slat so that the shoulder of the sleeper &quot;integrates&quot; well.
For men who have &quot;shoulders as wide as their backs&quot; this is really a big thing.
This thing is already being considered by mattress manufacturers, who for &quot;males&quot; have begun to use a softening zone in the shoulder area.
But they also think about women - again they offer them a softer surface on the hips.
For the more difficult customer there are wing or platelet bases with so-called multi-force suspension.
The pressure spreads to more points and decreases the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and inflated with air) on good mattresses and box springs, the &quot;plus&quot; disappears.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow should support the head, and its points should reach only the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm which Scandinavians for example prefer.
When lying on your side, the pillow should level (with the shoulder cradle of the box spring or the softened area in the mattress) the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first ones made from straw and grass.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also towards organic mattresses.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all well-known manufacturers use soybeans.
&quot;The qualifier Bio for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products&quot;, explains Petr vasicek of the company Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress coverings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop scents of the forest or lavender.
There are differences between man and woman.
While the birch plant extract for the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, &quot;cools&quot; the man, the covers &quot;heat&quot; the women.
Red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore hotter for the weaker sex.
Current favourites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disrupted cell structure therefore more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different stiffnesses of cold foams results in polyzone mattresses that know precisely where the head, lower back and feet are.
You will pay for a quality mattress from 7000 crowns and more.
Those that are characterized by their health parameters have less TVA and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex took first place.
Saving for the mattress and box spring is not easy.
One can from time to time have within the framework of special actions on behalf of the manufacturers or the producers two mattresses for the price of only one.
Like for example the company Magniflex which offers Duofreeze mattresses with Memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
You can obviously take the second one for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cell structure and great thickness was started with Tempur material at a &quot;cosmic&quot; pace.
It started out as material for NASA because astronauts started out with enormous load factors.
Tempur softens in the heat and hardens, on the contrary, in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes optimal pressure to it.
It is therefore ideal against bad sleep and for increased comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and the venous system.
Czech manufacturers use, for example, EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or similar.
Devices to track people are increasingly requested by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars, can just as well be used to trace the movement of people and help with certain cases such as that of little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved many people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
&quot;We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but just another way to decrease the likelihood of another tragedy,&quot; says Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, who is one of the suppliers of tracing devices on the Czech market.
&quot;I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of someone who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases. &quot;.
&quot;The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for safety reasons,&quot; adds Pilin.
According to him, children should always know what &quot;the box&quot; is used for and how to use it in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bockova draws attention that if the child does not want to wear such a thing, he will get rid of it.
&#39;And even the little ones can show great creativity when it comes to getting rid of something on purpose when they don&#39;t want to be under control&#39;.
&quot;Cellphones, which can shut themselves off like these tracking devices, have already caused parents to have long waits,&quot; Bockova says.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in the event of an attack is very questionable.
&quot;If it is a prepared abduction, the perpetrator will do everything so that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him&quot;.
“Currently, it is the telephone”.
“As soon as the tracing devices are developed, they (the criminals) will look for them too because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign”.
&quot;In such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police&quot;, says the psychologist.
She admits all the same that such devices can help during an unprepared aggression by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracing services for both cars and people, says having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an attack. .
&quot;The device can be configured in such a way that it is in regular transmission after a determined period&quot;.
&quot;In the event that the device is destroyed, there is still the last position of the person concerned&quot;.
&quot;The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately reports the position of the person who has slipped and ends up in a lying position without moving,&quot; says Cech.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system can offer a comparable service after formatting it with special software.
The problem with current tracing systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn as a pendant the size of a matchbox or to the smallest telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina from Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
&quot;This will have the advantage that the would-be attacker will not be able to recognize the tracking device.&quot;
“Or he will realize after a while, which will have given the police a little more time,” he adds.
Whether the tracking device is developed as a bracelet or a pendant, it will still use the same technology as for tracking cars.
It is a combination of systems for acquiring a position by means of GPS (which is commonly used in self-navigation) and a function of a mobile phone which alerts the current position of a vehicle.
