At the Land Fund in Plzen, police made arrests during a public competition
In the building of the Land Fund in Pilsen, anti-corruption police have been making arrests in recent days.
Detectives handcuffed local entrepreneur and real estate trader Lubos. G.
The latter had endeavored to manipulate a public call for tenders for the settlement of a claim for restitution in such a way that the land offered was obtained by a specific candidate.
He was to pay Lubos G. half a million crowns.
&quot;At this time I can only confirm that the police are prosecuting a person for insider trading in a public tender and competition.&quot; declared for the newspaper Pravo the chief of the Prosecutor&#39;s office of Plzen Antonie Zelena, knowing that it is prohibited to provide more explanations because the investigation is in hand.
The police released the 46-year-old entrepreneur after 24 hours.
To know how he could influence a public competition, one can only speculate given the so little official information.
To a question from Pravo, Land Fund spokeswoman Lubomira Cerna said that the police had actually made an arrest in Plzen at a separate workplace and this during the public competition.
&quot;It was a client and in no way an employee,&quot; she said.
The public competition according to Cerna has the real name &quot;Call to propose rights for the transfer of land according to the Land Law&quot; and is set up when several candidates who are beneficiaries of rights appear.
“These people are offering, as part of the appeal, a higher value of their restitution rights which must be settled before the value of the land is announced”.
&quot;According to the rights offered, a classification of buyers is put in place and the Land Fund then transfers the land to the person who offered the highest rights&quot;, explained the spokesperson for the Fund.
Lubos G. had, it is clear, the information concerning the people who had registered for the call and since he himself is also a beneficiary because having bought a large number of rights to restitutions, he had proposed candidates in the field not to participate in the competition.
And he probably cashed in by withdrawing.
Which would explain why he had so much money in his possession at the time of his arrest.
Lubos G. had contacts well above the standards at the FdT (Land Fund).
