Over one year, the unemployment rate rose by 0.1 points.
More broadly, 3.4 million people in mainland France were not working in the third quarter but wanted to work, whether or not they were available within two weeks to work and whether or not they were looking for a job.
The situation of young people on the labor market deteriorated further, with a further rise in the unemployment rate, to 24.2% in mainland France (+0.9 points over three months, +0.5 points over one year) and 25% including the overseas departments.
