Seniors, for their part, experienced a slight increase in unemployment, to 6.4% in mainland France (+0.2 points over three months as well as over one year), i.e. 482,000 people aged 50 or over, and 6.6 % with the DOMs.
Only 25-49 year olds benefited from stable unemployment in the third quarter, at 8.3% in mainland France (-0.1 point over three months, +0.1 point over one year) and 8.8% in the whole of France.
INSEE has not published a monthly unemployment rate since 2006, after a controversy over its calculation method.
